{{fr-noun|f-p}}

# {{lb|fr|dated|plurale tantum}} the [[churching]] of a woman; a ceremony at church to [[bless]] a woman who has recently [[give birth|given birth]]
#* {{quote-book|fr|text=À peine la messe de '''relevailles''' dite, Chiara apprend que ses trois enfants, nés d’un premier lit, sont morts de la peste à Milan et qu’elle doit se séparer de Girolamo, dont le père se juge seul capable de dispenser la première éducation.|year=2018|author=Daniel Barthes|chapter= La genèse des imaginaires |title=Les nombres complexes|publisher=Bibliothèque Tangente|page=8|t=The '''churching''' mass had barely been said when Chiara learned that the three children of her first marriage had died of the plague in Milan, and that she had to separate from Girolamo, whose father considered himself able of raising the child alone.}}
# {{lb|fr|dated|plurale tantum}} a woman's first time standing back up, or more generally, her period of recovery, after having given birth
#* {{quote-book|fr|year=1974|author=Marguerite Yourcenar|title=Souvenirs pieux|page=129|publisher=Collection Folio|text=Les '''relevailles''' d’un dame signifient à l’époque six semaines de chaise longue (les paysannes seules retournent au travail au bout de quelques jours, ce qui prouve la rudesse de ces femmes du peuple) […]|t=At the time, a lady's '''recovery after giving birth''' meant six weeks on a chaise longue (only peasant women returned to work after a few days, which proved how coarse these women of the people were) [...] }}
# {{lb|fr|plurale tantum}} assistance provided to the parents of a [[newborn]] baby
#* {{quote-web|fr|accessdate=2025-02-06|author=Espace-Famille Villeray|work=Relevailles|url=https://espacefamille.ca/relevailles/|text=Notre service de '''relevailles''' existe pour tous les parents de Villeray qui viennent d’accueillir un nouveau-né. Le service est disponible pendant 12 semaines pour les familles avec un enfant entre 0 et 12 mois.|t=Our '''support service for new parents''' is for all parents in Villeray who have just welcomed a newborn. The service is available for 12 weeks to families with a child between 0 and 12 months old.}}
